<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" version="2.0"><channel><title>blog of sarakure</title><link>https://sarakure13.github.io</link><description>Imagination within life.</description><copyright>blog of sarakure</copyright><docs>http://www.rssboard.org/rss-specification</docs><generator>python-feedgen</generator><image><url>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJOw6AhOyjxX6ET9kw00NMfvILzCxw0bYtIDwCLDcmWK6G-RGg=s200-c</url><title>avatar</title><link>https://sarakure13.github.io</link></image><lastBuildDate>Sat, 07 Mar 2026 04:37:49 +0000</lastBuildDate><managingEditor>blog of sarakure</managingEditor><ttl>60</ttl><webMaster>blog of sarakure</webMaster><item><title>Chapitre I: Du comique en général, Le comique des formes et le comique des mouvements, Force d’expansion du comique | 论喜剧的普遍性/形式的喜剧与动作的喜剧/喜剧的扩张力</title><link>https://sarakure13.github.io/post/Chapitre%20I-%20Du%20comique%20en%20g%C3%A9n%C3%A9ral%2C%20Le%20comique%20des%20formes%20et%20le%20comique%20des%20mouvements%2C%20Force%20d%E2%80%99expansion%20du%20comique%20-%20-lun-xi-ju-de-pu-bian-xing---xing-shi-de-xi-ju-yu-dong-zuo-de-xi-ju---xi-ju-de-kuo-zhang-li.html</link><description>笑意味着什么？可笑的本质究竟是什么？一个丑角的鬼脸、一个文字游戏、一场滑稽剧中的误会，或是一幕精妙喜剧的场景，它们之间究竟有何共通之处？我们如何从这些千差万别的产物中提炼出那始终如一的精华——那些产物或散发出粗俗的气息，或弥漫着微妙的芬芳？自亚里士多德以来，众多伟大思想家都曾试图解答这个看似微小却始终逃避探究的问题。</description><guid isPermaLink="true">https://sarakure13.github.io/post/Chapitre%20I-%20Du%20comique%20en%20g%C3%A9n%C3%A9ral%2C%20Le%20comique%20des%20formes%20et%20le%20comique%20des%20mouvements%2C%20Force%20d%E2%80%99expansion%20du%20comique%20-%20-lun-xi-ju-de-pu-bian-xing---xing-shi-de-xi-ju-yu-dong-zuo-de-xi-ju---xi-ju-de-kuo-zhang-li.html</guid><pubDate>Sat, 07 Mar 2026 02:59:55 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Préface: L’imagination matérielle et l’imagination parlée | 序言：物质的想象与言语的想象</title><link>https://sarakure13.github.io/post/Pr%C3%A9face-%20L%E2%80%99imagination%20mat%C3%A9rielle%20et%20l%E2%80%99imagination%20parl%C3%A9e%20-%20-xu-yan-%EF%BC%9A-wu-zhi-de-xiang-xiang-yu-yan-yu-de-xiang-xiang.html</link><description>在两卷书中，我们将推出第四部著作，致力于探讨物质的想象，即古代哲学与科学（由炼金术延续）所确立的四种基本物质元素的想象。</description><guid isPermaLink="true">https://sarakure13.github.io/post/Pr%C3%A9face-%20L%E2%80%99imagination%20mat%C3%A9rielle%20et%20l%E2%80%99imagination%20parl%C3%A9e%20-%20-xu-yan-%EF%BC%9A-wu-zhi-de-xiang-xiang-yu-yan-yu-de-xiang-xiang.html</guid><pubDate>Sat, 07 Mar 2026 02:15:31 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Introduction: Imagination Et Mobilité | 引言：想象力与流动性</title><link>https://sarakure13.github.io/post/Introduction-%20Imagination%20Et%20Mobilit%C3%A9%20-%20-yin-yan-%EF%BC%9A-xiang-xiang-li-yu-liu-dong-xing.html</link><description>与许多心理学问题一样，关于想象力的研究也被词源学的虚假光芒所困扰。</description><guid isPermaLink="true">https://sarakure13.github.io/post/Introduction-%20Imagination%20Et%20Mobilit%C3%A9%20-%20-yin-yan-%EF%BC%9A-xiang-xiang-li-yu-liu-dong-xing.html</guid><pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 12:32:26 +0000</pubDate></item></channel></rss>